				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twink Bard looking for some help<a name="42001"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 25 04 6:13 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Take a quick look at my twinked bard in my sig.  Most of my gear came off my older SK though, so its not the best designed stuff that you could get, but should give you an idea what some others are wearing/weilding.  Some definate stuff you might want to shoot for though...Bracelet of fortitude (playing a SK makes you learn the benefit of all the HPs you can get)...cloak of greater pernicity (one of the absolute best items I've ever gotten)...maybe one of the jeweled veils to match your necklace (I think velium is 10 dex 10 cha)...other than that, it depends on your playstyle mostly, do you need more CHA for charms/lulls/mezzes etc.  I'm a strong supporter that gear makes a good bard better.  I'm also for the fact that HP&gt;all.  HPs help if you group a lot as you'll be pulling most likely and need to be able to survive a few hits from time to time, and HPs help when soloing for those annoying lag spots or slight mistakes that cost a lot of people a lot of exp.  Then of course there's always...Your feet move faster.  Your feet slow down...generally followed by...Loading, please wait...</span></td>
